  <h2>Features</h2>

  <p>The randomizer can mix-up many aspects of the original levels, creating a unique experience each time you play, and at times some very interesting scenarios. Everything is optional so you can tune the outcome to your preference each time.</p>

  <h4>Items</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Change the location and type of each pickup item</li>
    <li>Key items can also be included for an additional challenge</li>
    <li>Create a one-item mode challenge</li>
    <li>Alter pickup appearance so you don't know what you're picking up each time</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Secrets</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Change the location of each secret (TR1 and TR3 use artefact pickups, similar to TR2)</li>
    <li>Choose between easy and hard mode and optionally include locations that require glitch knowledge</li>
    <li>Randomize the rewards you receive for collecting all secrets</li>
    <li>Change the appearance of pickup sprites</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Enemies</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Switch up the enemy types that appear in each level</li>
    <li>Filter out certain enemies according to preference</li>
    <li>Use a cloned enemy mode for an extra challenge in TR1</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Lara</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Change Lara's outfit</li>
    <li>Randomly add or remove Lara's braid</li>
    <li>Make Lara invisible</li>
    <li>Change Lara's starting position in the level</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Audio</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Change triggered music tracks</li>
    <li>Change ambient music</li>
    <li>Change the majority of sound effects</li>
    <li>Use uncontrolled SFX mode for a truly random experience</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Visuals</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Change various textures, from the skybox right down to to the colour of Lara's socks</li>
    <li>Choose to play levels at night, or to use the sunset effect in TR2 to gradually darken the level</li>
    <li>Choose various visual effects in TR3 such as vertex colouring and wave movement</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Environment</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Change water levels</li>
    <li>Move keyholes, levers and switches</li>
    <li>Randomize trap locations</li>
    <li>Add extra puzzle and challenge rooms</li>
    <li>Play mirrored levels</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Gameplay</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Change the order in which levels are played</li>
    <li>Change the number of levels to play in a game</li>
    <li>Change inventory text such as weapon and key names - includes 13 language options</li>
  </ul>

